                    <msContents>
                        <summary>
                            
                            <p>This is an important inscription in Sanskrit verse which states that the rock-cut shrine was caused to be made by king <hi rend="bold">Vichitrachitta</hi> for the enshrinement of the three gods Brahmā, Īśvara and Vishṇu, without the use of bricks, timber, metal and mortar. Since from Pallava inscriptions we know that Mahēndravarman I had the <hi rend="italic">biruda</hi> ‘Vichitra-chitta’ (i.e.) curious or fancy-minded, this cave must have been excavated by him.</p>	
                            
                        </summary>
